Let me analyze the target structure and provide a detailed solution.

Analysis of the Main Target Image:
- The structure has 3 distinct layers
- Bottom layer: An arched bridge-like structure (red/orange)
- Middle layer: Two cylindrical pillars (orange) with a yellow rectangular block on top
- Top layer: A triangular roof piece (orange) sitting on the yellow block

Block count and composition:
- 2 yellow rectangular blocks (horizontal orientation)
- 2 orange cylindrical pillars
- 1 orange triangular roof piece
- 1 arched base structure

Matching blocks from the dictionary:
- Yellow horizontal blocks: #6 and #8
- Orange cylinders: #9 (used twice)
- Orange triangular roof: #13
- Arched base structure: #1

Assembly order from bottom to top:
{
    Step1: Move block with index 1
    Step2: Move block with index 6
    Step3: Move block with index 9
    Step4: Move block with index 9
    Step5: Move block with index 8
    Step6: Move block with index 13
}

This assembly sequence will create the structure exactly as shown in the target image, maintaining all spatial relationships and orientations of the blocks.
